@mostaphaRoudsari ,

The structure generally looks good.  I will admit that I still do not fully understand how the images work but I trust that you have a solid understanding and will be able to implement it.  Let me know if you need any help navigating around the grasshopper component.  I tried to make the code as clean as possible.

-Chris

@chriswmackey, I modified the component and web pages to work with the new schema. They still support the old schema from Grasshopper but you will see a warning that the example is generated by an older version of Hydra.

Back to images [this example](http://hydrashare.github.io/hydra/viewer?owner=mostaphaRoudsari&fork=hydra_1&id=shadow_range_study) might help to make it clear. As you can see now you can document your example with more than Rhino and Grasshopper images. Think as a Hydra page like a blog post. You may have some images prepared for a specific purpose. I think you should be able to have them included in Hydra. Also not all the example files will be generated from Rhino and Grasshopper. That's why I changed the field to images to keep it generic and compatible with other platforms.

Let me know if it looks good to you and we can close this issue.

@mdahlhausen yes we are agnostic to image types. I changed the images to a list of objects so now order does matter. First image on the list will show up first. I modified it in the first comment on this page.

@chriswmackey users don't need to copy the files manually (however they can if they want). I added a new input to the component to add additional images and component takes care of copying the files.

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2915573/10270019/b079b750-6ab3-11e5-9058-7b67de50ee20.png)

As I mentioned above, the order is now fixed so Grasshopper image will always show up first unless user modifies the json file manually. Here is the [same example](http://hydrashare.github.io/hydra/viewer?owner=mostaphaRoudsari&fork=hydra_1&id=shadow_range_study) file exported with the new component, and Grasshopper definition will be always loaded first.

I took out the code for now until we make sure it works fine:

``` javascript

// tracking example files and downloads!
    jQuery(document).ready(function( $ ) {
        var request;
        // bind the download submit event to the form
        $("#example-download").submit(function(event){
            //download the zip file from github
            window.location = example.download_path;

            // abort any pending request
            if (request) {  
                request.abort();
            }

            // setup some local variables
            var $form = $(this);        
            var $inputs = $form.find("button");
            $inputs.prop("disabled", true);
            $('#downloadCount').text('#');      
            data={"owner":example.owner,"description":example.description,"request_type":"increment"};

            // fire off the request to /form.php
            request = $.ajax({
                url: "https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbxiRnl-119Qy-Ygchrjp5OiMelYUJCZ-ZHjpwKTm6dtaYCOZ9IZ/exec",
                type: "post",
                data: data
            });

            // callback handler that will be called on success
            request.done(function (response, textStatus, jqXHR){
                // log a message to the console
                $('#downloadCount').text(response.downloads);
                console.log(response);
            });
            // callback handler that will be called on failure
            request.fail(function (jqXHR, textStatus, errorThrown){
                // log the error to the console
                console.error("The following error occured: " + textStatus, errorThrown);
            });
            // callback handler that will be called regardless if the request failed or succeeded
            request.always(function () {
                // reenable the inputs
                $inputs.prop("disabled", false);
            });

            // prevent default posting of form
            event.preventDefault();
        });
    });
```

